The diagram above shows the process of data securely traveling from a client to
a server and safely processed. At first the client prepares data from a web
browser, mobile app or computer. After that the data is encoded and is formatted
correctly before sending. It prevents special characters from breaking the
request and helps prevent injection attacks. It also ensures compatibility
between the systems. After encoding the data is encrypted using TLS which
ensures secure HTTPS connection. It protects the data while it is traveling over
the internet. After that the data reaches the server and TLS decrypts the
message. Only the intended server can decrypt and read the message. Finally the
server decodes the data and the data is processed by application. After all
those steps at the end the database stores or retrieves information.
